16/04/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- UN Secretary General Kofi Annan will meet on Wednesday (16 April) in Athens with British Prime Minister Tony Blair, German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder and the foreign ministers of France, Germany, Russia, Spain and the UK. They gathered to attend the EU summit that begins Wednesday and will result in the official signing of the EU Accession Acts with ten new members of the Union.
In other news, the EU approved a revised version of the Accession Partnership Accord with Turkey on Tuesday. Ankara says it makes no significant changes from the previous version. The government hopes to start EU accession talks by the end of 2004. (UN News Centre, ANA, MPA, CAN, Dnevnik, Anadolu Agency, NTV, AFP - 15/04/03)
